Since $x:y = 3:1$, we can assume $x = 3$ and $y = 1$. Substituting these directly into the expression:

$$
\frac{x^3 - y^3}{x^3 + y^3}
=
\frac{3^3 - 1^3}{3^3 + 1^3}
=
\frac{27 - 1}{27 + 1}
=
\frac{26}{28}
=
\frac{13}{14}
$$

Hence, the ratio is $13:14$.

