Factor out 4 from the second term:

$$
\sqrt{(3 + \sqrt{2}) \times 4(3 - \sqrt{2})}
$$

Use the difference of squares identity $(a+b)(a-b) = a^2 - b^2$:

$$
\sqrt{4(3^2 - (\sqrt{2})^2)}
=
\sqrt{4(9 - 2)}
=
\sqrt{4 \times 7}
=
